title: Plane hit by bullets and two killed in failed $32m airport heist
description: Two people have been killed in an airport shoot-out in Chile's capital in what authorities said was an attempted heist of more than $32m in cash aboard a plane from Miami.

title: China-US tensions set to be defining issue of our time as TikTok 'threat' alarms Washington
description: One revealing exchange spelt out the reason that America's top intelligence officials believe TikTok is a threat to US national security.

title: TikTok 'screams' of US national security concerns, FBI chief warns
description: The Chinese government could use TikTok to control the data of millions of American users, according to the FBI.

title: Leading Chinese genetics firm tried to hack NHS genome database, claims minister
description: A leading Chinese genetics firm has been accused by a government minister of trying to hack the NHS genome database.

title: Ireland to hold vote on 'women's place in the home' constitution reference
description: Ireland will hold a vote in November on removing "outmoded" references to a woman's place being in the home from the country's constitution.

title: Argentina targets $500m in cannabis sales and 10,000 jobs as it eyes up export market
description: Argentina's government says it is hoping to achieve $500m (£422m) in domestic cannabis sales and $50m in exports by 2025.

title: Child injured amid reports of gunshots at home of NFL star Joe Mixon
description: Police have searched the home of NFL star Joe Mixon following reports of gunshots at the property in Cincinnati, Ohio.

title: Elon Musk apologises after mocking sacked Twitter worker in online row
description: Twitter boss Elon Musk has backpedalled after publicly mocking an employee on the social media platform.

title: Pro-Ukraine group calls on Academy to 'review eligibility' of Top Gun: Maverick for Oscars
description: The Ukrainian World Congress (UWC) has urged organisers of the Academy Awards to "review the eligibility" of the Top Gun sequel for this year's ceremony, due to the film's alleged ties to a Russian oligarch.

title: Bindi Irwin was told endometriosis 'simply something you deal with as a woman' as she reveals 10-year struggle
description: Bindi Irwin, daughter of the late Australian wildlife presenter Steve Irwin, has revealed her decade-long struggle with endometriosis in an emotional social media post.

title: Pro-Ukrainian group 'responsible for Nord Stream pipeline attacks', US intelligence suggests
description: US intelligence suggests a pro-Ukraine group was responsible for the damage caused to Nord Stream gas pipelines, according to reports.
